b'Watch little entrepreneur Treandos see his holiday wish come true.

Treandos started his own bow tie company after he was inspired by seeing his dad wearing them. The business wasn\xe2\x80\x99t just about fashion though, it was about making people feel good and confident. This led Treandos to want to make a positive change in his community and help those suffering from food insecurity. With the help of our drivers, we made his wish come true. First, Treandos and his younger brother Noah delivered bow ties to UPS drivers at the UPS hub in Atlanta. But what he didn\xe2\x80\x99t know was he was about to get a very special delivery: a UPS truck filled with food and toys to be donated in his name to United Food Force. And, of course, the confidence that comes from knowing you don\xe2\x80\x99t have to be a grownup to make a difference. 

To see more #WishesDelivered, visit us at http://ups.com/wishes'

b'It\xe2\x80\x99s golf\xe2\x80\x99s most famous Clubhouse \xe2\x80\x93 not a blade of grass or lick of paint out of place. A fair bit of elbow grease goes into keeping it that way.
